RA: local DB needed, but no subprocess/external API required. MOCK-HIDE: yes, mocked transaction APIs often do not reproduce real SQL failure/rollback behavior. LLM-DEP/MULTI-STEP: no.","test_description":"Use three migrations: first writes data, second contains a failing SQL statement after a prior write in the same migration transaction, third writes a marker. Run runner against local Postgres and assert second migration produced no partial writes (rolled back), third was not applied, and `_migrations` includes only successful prior migrations.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.84,"System":0.09,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"When two instances of the runner start at the same time against the same database, each migration is applied exactly once across both instances.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"MOCK-MISS: yes—race conditions appear only with real concurrent runners. REAL-INFRA: yes—requires separate processes and real DB locking/constraints under contention. MOCK-HIDE: yes, in-process mocks/serialized execution can falsely pass. LLM-DEP/MULTI-STEP: no.","test_description":"Spawn two Node.js runner subprocesses simultaneously against the same Postgres test DB and identical migration directory. Include migrations with observable one-time side effects. Assert both processes exit successfully (or one no-op after coordination), each migration’s side effect appears exactly once, and `_migrations` has exactly one row per migration.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.12,"System":0.85,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"On the very first run against a fresh database, the `_migrations` table is created before any migration file is applied.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: yes—bootstrap ordering depends on real DB schema initialization an